com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.setup

类 AylaSetup

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.setup.AylaSetup

  • public class AylaSetup
extends java.lang.Object
    The AylaSetup class is used to scan for devices that are in AP mode, or in other words have not yet been configured to join the local WiFi network. Devices that are not able to join a WiFi network will put themselves into AP mode and broadcast an SSID that is identifiable as an Ayla device.

    Once a device's AP has been discovered via a call to scanForAccessPoints(int, com.android.internal.util.Predicate<android.net.wifi.ScanResult>, com.android.volley.Response.Listener<android.net.wifi.ScanResult[]>, com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.error.ErrorListener), the result can be passed to connectToNewDevice(java.lang.String, int, com.android.volley.Response.Listener<com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.setup.AylaSetupDevice>, com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.error.ErrorListener) to connect the mobile device to the device's AP. Once the mobile device and setup device are connected this way, the mobile device asks the setup device to do its own scan for access points via scanForAccessPoints(int, com.android.internal.util.Predicate<android.net.wifi.ScanResult>, com.android.volley.Response.Listener<android.net.wifi.ScanResult[]>, com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.error.ErrorListener), which returns another set of access points.

    At this point the user may choose an access point she wishes the device to connect to and supply the app with the WiFi password. Once this is done, a call to connectDeviceToService(java.lang.String, java.lang.String, java.lang.String, java.lang.Double, java.lang.Double, int, com.android.volley.Response.Listener<com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.setup.AylaWifiStatus>, com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.error.ErrorListener) will provide the setup device with the AP SSID and password.

    At that point, the device will attempt to connect to the specified AP using the supplied password. This of course will drop our connection with the setup device's AP, where we will re-join the network we were previously connected to.

    In order to confirm that the device has successfully connected to the WiFi network, and subsequently the Ayla service, the confirmDeviceConnected(int, java.lang.String, java.lang.String, com.android.volley.Response.Listener<com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.setup.AylaSetupDevice>, com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.error.ErrorListener) method can be called to verify that the device has connected.

    Once the device has been connected to the network, it may be registered to the user's account if it was not already registered (e.g. WiFi password or SSID changed, etc.).

    To ensure that the mobile device has returned to its original WiFi network, call exitSetup(com.android.volley.Response.Listener<com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.AylaAPIRequest.EmptyResponse>, com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.error.ErrorListener) and wait for the response to ensure the network is configured as it was before starting setup operations.

      • scanForAccessPoints

        public AylaAPIRequest scanForAccessPoints(int timeoutInSeconds,
                                          com.android.internal.util.Predicate<android.net.wifi.ScanResult> filter,
                                          com.android.volley.Response.Listener<android.net.wifi.ScanResult[]> successListener,
                                          ErrorListener errorListener)
        Scans for wireless access points visible to the mobile device and returns the list of APs. This is used to find devices near the mobile device that have not yet been configured to join the local WiFi network. Ayla devices have SSIDs that have recognizable names, which can be used to filter the result set via a Predicate filter that may be passed to this method.

        Once a suitable access point has been found, applications should call connectToNewDevice(java.lang.String, int, com.android.volley.Response.Listener<com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.setup.AylaSetupDevice>, com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.error.ErrorListener) to connect the mobile device to the device, and then have the device scan for visible WiFi access points.

        参数:
        timeoutInSeconds - Maximum time to spend scanning for APs, in seconds. If the scan does not complete in the specified time, the caller's errorListener will be called with a TimeoutError.
        filter - An optional Predicate that can be used to filter the result set
        successListener - Listener to receive the list of scan results
        errorListener - Listener to receive an error if one should occur
        返回:
        an AylaAPIRequest, which may be canceled to stop the scan. If the scan is canceled the errorListener will be called with a TimeoutError. Other errors that may be passed to the errorListener include:
        • AppPermissionError on M and above if permissions were not granted
        • PreconditionError on M and above if Location Services are not turned on
        • TimeoutError if the scan timed out

      • scanAPsWithRegex

        public AylaAPIRequest scanAPsWithRegex(int timeoutInSeconds,
                                       java.lang.String scanRegex,
                                       com.android.volley.Response.Listener<android.net.wifi.ScanResult[]> successListener,
                                       ErrorListener errorListener)
        Scans for wireless access points visible to the mobile device and returns the list of APs. This is used to find devices near the mobile device that have not yet been configured to join the local WiFi network. Ayla devices have SSIDs that have recognizable names, which can be used to filter the result set via a Predicate filter that may be passed to this method.

        Once a suitable access point has been found, applications should call connectToNewDevice(java.lang.String, int, com.android.volley.Response.Listener<com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.setup.AylaSetupDevice>, com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.error.ErrorListener) to connect the mobile device to the device, and then have the device scan for visible WiFi access points.

        参数:
        timeoutInSeconds - Maximum time to spend scanning for APs, in seconds. If the scan does not complete in the specified time, the caller's errorListener will be called with a TimeoutError.
        scanRegex - A Regular expression which is used to filter the result set, all wifi ssid from returned result will match regex
        successListener - Listener to receive the list of scan results
        errorListener - Listener to receive an error if one should occur
        返回:
        an AylaAPIRequest, which may be canceled to stop the scan. If the scan is canceled the errorListener will be called with a TimeoutError. Other errors that may be passed to the errorListener include:
        • AppPermissionError on M and above if permissions were not granted
        • PreconditionError on M and above if Location Services are not turned on
        • TimeoutError if the scan timed out

      • confirmDeviceConnected

        public AylaAPIRequest confirmDeviceConnected(int timeoutInSeconds,
                                             java.lang.String dsn,
                                             java.lang.String setupToken,
                                             com.android.volley.Response.Listener<AylaSetupDevice> successListener,
                                             ErrorListener errorListener)
        Confirms that the setup device has connected to the Ayla service. The mobile device needs to be able to reach the Device service in order for this call to succeed. Make sure the mobile device has called reconnectToOriginalNetwork(int, com.android.volley.Response.Listener<com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.AylaAPIRequest.EmptyResponse>, com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.error.ErrorListener) before making this call to ensure we are not connected to the module's access point.
        参数:
        timeoutInSeconds - Timeout for this operation.
        dsn - DSN of the device to confirm
        setupToken - Setup token passed to the device in connectDeviceToService(java.lang.String, java.lang.String, java.lang.String, java.lang.Double, java.lang.Double, int, com.android.volley.Response.Listener<com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.setup.AylaWifiStatus>, com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.error.ErrorListener)
        successListener - Listener called when the device has been confirmed to connect to the service. The listener will be called with an AylaSetupDevice containing at least the LAN IP address, device type, registration type and time the device connected.
        errorListener - Listener called if an error occurs or the operation times out
        返回:
        the AylaAPIRequest for this request

      • reconnectToOriginalNetwork

        public AylaAPIRequest reconnectToOriginalNetwork(int timeoutInSeconds,
                                                 com.android.volley.Response.Listener<AylaAPIRequest.EmptyResponse> successListener,
                                                 ErrorListener errorListener)
        Connects the mobile device to the WiFi network it was connected to when we joined the device's access point. If a previous call to connectDeviceToService(java.lang.String, java.lang.String, java.lang.String, java.lang.Double, java.lang.Double, int, com.android.volley.Response.Listener<com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.setup.AylaWifiStatus>, com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.error.ErrorListener) was not made prior to calling this method, it will fail with a PreconditionError.
        参数:
        timeoutInSeconds - Maximum time to spend trying to reconnect. A TimeoutError will be delivered to the ErrorListener if this time is exceeded before we are able to join the network.
        successListener - Listener called when we have successfully re-joined the network
        errorListener - Listener called if we fail to join the network in the specified time period.
        返回:
        the AylaAPIRequest that may be canceled to stop this operation

      • disconnectAPMode

        public AylaAPIRequest disconnectAPMode(com.android.volley.Response.Listener<AylaAPIRequest.EmptyResponse> successListener,
                                       ErrorListener errorListener)
        disconnectAPMode method is used to Shut down AP Mode on the module. This method is typically not used by the Client Apps as the AP Mode will be shut down automatically in 30 seconds when the device is connected to service. Method only works when android device is connected to module. On success, an HTTP status of “204 No Content” is returned. Otherwise, an HTTP status of “403 Forbidden” is returned. AP mode disconnect command is only accepted when module is still in AP mode, and successfully connected to service in STA mode (i.e STA mode and AP mode are active at the same time). This command turns off the AP mode, leaving STA mode active only.
        参数:
        successListener - Listener called When the disconnect AP Mode is success
        errorListener - Listener called in case of errors
        返回:
        the AylaAPIRequest for this request

      • exitSetup

        public AylaAPIRequest exitSetup(com.android.volley.Response.Listener<AylaAPIRequest.EmptyResponse> successListener,
                                ErrorListener errorListener)
        Exits the setup process. This call will re-connect the mobile device to the AP it was connected to at the start of the setup process, and clean up any internal state information. DO NOT RE-USE an AylaSetup object after its exitSetup() method is called.
        参数:
        successListener - Listener called when the operation succeeds
        errorListener - Listener called if the operation encountered an error
        返回:
        an AylaAPIRequest that may be used to cancel this operation, or null if the operation may not be canceled (e.g. we are already on the original WiFi network or the original AP was not saved)
